0insulin%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20actor's%20life%20can%20appear%20glamorous%20to%20the%20outside%20world%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20often%20anything%20but%2C%20says%20the%2040-year-old.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20%26quot%3B99%20percent%20of%20actors%2C%26quot%3B%20daily%20life%20is%20spent%20%26quot%3Bon%20the%20ground%2C%20auditioning%20and%20hustling%20and%20fighting%20to%20get%20in%20audition%20rooms.%26quot%3B%20And%20that%20is%20when%20they%20are%20not%20working%20part-time%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20six%20years%20he%20lived%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20Burgess%20worked%20part-time%20at%20the%20local%20Arclight%20movie%20theater%2C%20for%20%247.75%20per%20hour%2C%20to%20supplement%20his%20meager%20acting%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20he%20says%20he%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bfortunate%20to%20be%20able%20to%20sustain%20myself%20through%20acting%2C%26quot%3B%20landing%20guest%20roles%20in%20shows%20like%20Netflix's%20Emmy-nominated%20%3Ci%3EDahmer%20-%20Monster%3A%20The%20Jeffrey%20Dahmer%20Story%3C%2Fi%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20%26quot%3Bday-to-day%2C%20I'm%20very%20proactive.%20I%20have%20a%20manager%20who%20I%20adore%2C%20and%20we%20sniff%20out%20work%20where%20we%20can.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnsustainable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20actors%20earn%20their%20living%20through%20a%20mixture%20of%20wages%20when%20they%20are%20actively%20working%2C%20along%20with%20%26quot%3Bresiduals%26quot%3B%20--%20payments%20for%20shows%20and%20films%20they%20previously%20appeared%20in%2C%20which%20are%20still%20being%20rewatched%20by%20audiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20of%20these%20have%20dwindled%20over%20the%20years%2C%20said%20Burgess%2C%20as%20studios%20and%20networks%20keep%20%26quot%3Bsqueezing%2C%20forcing%20everyone%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20real%20trend%20of%20late%2C%20especially%20with%20streamers%2C%20is%20that%20they%20won't%20pay%20above%20'scale'%20-%20you're%20working%20for%20the%20bare%20minimum%20that%20you're%20legally%20allowed%20to%20work%20for%20under%20SAG%20rules%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20worked%20for%20a%20company%20this%20year%20that%20I%20worked%20for%20in%202012%2C%20and%20I'm%20being%20paid%20less%20for%20my%20services%20this%20year%20than%20I%20was%2010%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20union%20minimum%20salaries%20that%20most%20actors%20earn%20can%20appear%20misleadingly%20high%2C%20explained%20Burgess.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20day%20rate%20for%20a%20television%20performer%20is%20%241%2C082%2C%20around%20half%20of%20that%20disappears%20to%20agents%2C%20legal%20fees%20and%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20then%2C%20an%20actor%20being%20paid%20for%20just%20one%20or%20two%20days'%20work%20may%20be%20required%20to%20hold%20several%20weeks%20free%20for%20a%20shoot%2C%20as%20the%20producers%20work%20out%20their%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20pretty%20common%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Burgess.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20then%20that%20%24500%20has%20to%20stretch%20you%20for%20eight%20days%2C%20or%2016%20days%2C%20or%2021%20days%20if%20it's%20a%20prestige%20drama%20-%20it%20becomes%20very%20unsustainable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20cost-cutting%20measures%20are%20becoming%20ever%20more%20common%2C%20such%20as%20downgrading%20%26quot%3Bseries%20regulars%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Brecurring%20guest%20stars%26quot%3B%20or%20even%20one-day%20guest%20stars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20goal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20all%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20what%20Burgess%20expected%20when%20he%20arrived%20in%20the%20United%20States%20some%2016%20years%20ago.%20%26quot%3BLA%20was%20always%20the%20goal%20for%20me%2C%20because%20I%20was%20raised%20on%20'X-Files'%20and%20'Buffy'%20and%20'Twin%20Peaks'%20and%20'Star%20Trek.'%20They%20were%20the%20shows%20that%20I%20