articleshow%2F101741138.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22French%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20awarded%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20with%20the%20highest%20French%20honour%2C%20the%20Grand%20Cross%20of%20the%20Legion%20of%20Honour.%20The%20ceremony%20was%20held%20at%20the%20Elysee%20Palace%20as%20part%20of%20Modi's%20two-day%20visit%20to%20Paris.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fgrand-cross-of-the-legion-of-honour-pm-modi-conferred-with-frances-highest-honour%2Farticleshow%2F101741138.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20What%20China%20Really%20Thinks%20Of%20India's%20'Neutrality'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Cold%20War%20between%20the%20US%20and%20the%20former%20Soviet%20Union%20ended%20in%201991%2C%20a%20reading%20of%20how%20powerful%20states%20of%20the%20time%20behaved%20continues%20to%20dictate%20foreign%20policy%20thinking%2C%20even%20in%20the%20current%20epoch%20of%20international%20relations.%20India%20and%20China%2C%20both%20newly%20independent%20states%20in%20the%20post-World%20War%20II%20era%2C%20lacking%20adequate%20economic%20and%20political%20standing%20in%20international%20politics%20in%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%2C%20emerged%20as%20important%20voices.%20India's%20non-aligned%20policies%2C%20which%20focused%20on%20neutrality%20between%20the%20two%20power%20blocs%2C%20gained%20a%20lot%20of%20traction%20and%20was%20seen%20as%20an%20important%20tool%20to%20shield%20national%20interests%20from%20Cold%20War%20dynamics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%2C%20which%20was%20officially%20%26quot%3Bleaning%20to%20one%20side%26quot%3B%2C%20or%20to%20the%20side%20of%20communism%20led%20by%20the%20USSR%2C%20also%20emerged%20as%20an%20important%20voice%20in%20international%20politics%2C%20as%20it%20joined%20the%20Korean%20War%20in%201950%20against%20the%20so-called%20onslaught%20of%20capitalist%20and%20imperialist%20forces.%20At%20the%20Bandung%20conference%20of%20Asian-African%20countries%20in%201955%2C%20where%20the%20idea%20of%20non-alignment%20took%20deeper%20roots%2C%20Chinese%20Premier%20Zhou%20Enlai's%20speech%20was%20highly%20appreciated%2C%20as%20he%20spoke%20of%20%26quot%3Bseeking%20common%20grounds%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bnot%20seeking%20divergences%26quot%3B.%20Seemingly%2C%20India's%20and%20China's%20stands%20looked%20alike.%20A%20closer%20reading%2C%20however%2C%20reveals%20many%20differences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20worth%20discussing%20questions%20around%20neutrality%20as%20a%20foreign%20policy%20choice%20in%202023%2C%20given%20that%20both%20India%20and%20China%2C%20once%20again%2C%20have%20largely%20chosen%20diplomatically%20neutral%20stances%20at%20the%20UN%20in%20the%20ongoing%20Russia-Ukraine%20war.%20The%20fallout%20of%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20continues%20to%20be%20discussed%20at%20various%20regional%20and%20multilateral%20forums%2C%20and%20the%20most%20recent%20instance%20of%20these%20discussions%20was%20the%20virtual%20summit%20of%20the%20Shanghai%20Cooperation%20Organization%20(SCO)%20hosted%20by%20India.%20While%20Russia%20spoke%20of%20the%20need%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Btruly%20just%20and%20multipolar%20world%26quot%3B%2C%20China%20spoke%20about%20the%20need%20for%20members%20to%20%26quot%3Bprotect%20and%20promote%20their%20security%20and%20development%20interests%26quot%3B.%20India%20spoke%20about%20the%20need%20to%20deepen%20cooperation%20for%20sustainable%20socio-economic%20development%20and%20to%20improve%20the%20well-being%20and%20living%20standards%20of%20the%20people%20in%20the%20SCO%20region.%20India%20also%20criticised%20the%20international%20scourge%20of%20terrorism.%20What%20also%20stands%20out%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20India%20refused%20to%20sign%20the%20SCO's%20economic%20development%20strategy%20for%202030%20due%20to%20objections%20over%20retaining%20language%20that%20echoed%20Chinese%20official%20policies.%20In%20essence%2C%20India%20did%20not%20sign%20onto%20China's%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%20(BRI)%20which%20is%20violative%20of%20India's%20sovereignty%2C%20among%20other%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20statements%20at%20the%20SCO%20make%20it%20clear%20that%20it%20does%20not%20want%20to%20be%20embroiled%20in%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%2C%20but%20it%20does%20want%20to%20address%20the%20fallout%20of%20the%20crisis%20on%20developing%20countries%2C%20including%20India.%20This%20is%20why%20New%20Delhi%20spoke%20of%20how%20existing%20conflicts%20are%20aggravating%20and%20new%20conflicts%20are%20emerging.%20India's%20position%2C%20particularly%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20is%20rooted%20in%20its%20time-tested%20policies%20of%20non-alignment%2C%20which%20hinge%20on%20neutrality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20and%20China%2C%20both%20important%20movers%20and%20shakers%20in%20international%20politics%2C%20could%20have%20taken%20the%20mantle%20of%20the%20developing%20world%20together.%20However%2C%20deep%20divergences%20in%20the%20world%20views%20of%20the%20two%20hinder%20a%20cooperative%20approach.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20it%20becomes%20pertinent%20to%20understand%20what%20China%20really%20thinks%20of%20India's%20neutrality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20time%20a%20state%20visit%20takes%20place%20between%20India%20and%20the%20US%2C%20the%20Chinese%20media%20goes%20overboard%20emphasising%20how%20India%20has%20always%20been%20neutral%20and%20the%20US%20is%20instrumental%20in%20driving%20a%20wedge%20between%20India%20and%20China%2C%20while%20completely%20ignoring%20the%20aggressive%20stance%20China%20takes%20against%20India%20in%20multiple%20avenues%20of%20the%20bilateral%20relationship.%20These%20statements%20are%20found%20in%20abundance%20even%20after%20the%20recent%20Modi-Biden%20meeting%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bonhomie%20between%20India%20and%20the%20US%20does%20not%20work%20well%20for%20China%20for%20the%20simple%20reason%20that%20the%20two%20are%20democracies%2C%20have%20similar%20systems%20of%20governance%2C%20and%20are%20not%20revisionist%20powers.%20While%20China%20touts%20India's%20neutrality%20and%20says%20it%20should%20stay%20neutral%20in%20all%20conflicts%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%2C%20Beijing%20does%20not%20really%20think%20highly%20of%20'neutrality'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalyst%20Pan%20Guang's%20recent%20interview%20on%20the%20role%20of%20the%20SCO%2C%20published%20on%20the%20Chinese%20news%20website%20Guancha%2C%20mentions%20India's%20neutral%20positions%20in%20foreign%20policy%20and%20is%20an%20important%20indicator%20to%20understand%20what%20China%20thinks%20of%20India's%20neutrality.%20Dr.%20Pan%2C%20an%20SCO%20practitioner%2C%20stated%20in%20his%20interview%20that%20he%20does%20not%20think%20India%20has%20fallen%20into%20the%20US%20orbit%2C%20and%20that%20India%20has%20not%20explicitly%20stated%20that%20it%20has%20shifted%20to%20one%20side%20-%20not%20yet.%20India%2C%20he%20says%2C%20has%20insisted%20on%20having%20it%20both%20ways%20or%20%26quot%3Bto%20put%20it%20diplomatically...%20on%20being%20nonaligned%26quot%3B.%20The%20interview%20in%20Chinese%20uses%20the%20phrase%20%3Cem%3E'jiao%20ta%20liang%20tiao%20chuan'%3C%2Fem%3E%20which%20literally%20translates%20into%20'traveling%20in%20two%20boats'.%20However%2C%20the%20concept%20of%20traveling%20in%20two%20boats%20is%20not%20what%20India's%20non-alignment%20or%20neutrality%20means.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr.%20Pan's%20use%20of%20the%20phrase%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20Mao%20Zedong's%20statements%20on%20India's%20foreign%20policy%20choices%20during%20the%20Cold%20War.%20%26quot%3BTo%20sit%20on%20the%20fence%20is%20impossible.%20A%20third%20road%20does%20not%20exist%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20had%20said.%20He%20had%20emphasised%20on%20the%20need%20to%20either%20take%20the%20side%20of%20imperialism%20or%20socialism.%20He%20had%20also%20referred%20to%20India's%20decision%20to%20join%20the%20commonwealth%20as%20a%20phenomenon%20where%20India%2C%20like%20an%20insecure%20child%2C%20is%20tied%20to%20the%20apron%20strings%20of%20its%20colonial%20masters.%20Of%20course%2C%20there%20has%20never%20been%20any%20attempt%20from%20China%20to%20understand%20India's%20rationale%20for%20its%20foreign%20policy%20choices%20or%20national%20interests%2C%20and%20the%20outdated%20and%20incorrect%20Chinese%20understanding%20of%20India's%20neutrality%20permeates%20from%20Mao%20Zedong's%20times%20to%20Xi%20Jinping's.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20must%20understand%20the%20deep%20divergences%20between%20India%20and%20China%2C%20and%20refrain%20from%20using%20any%20statement%20or%20phrase%20that%20the%20Chinese%20use%20in%20international%20politics%2C%20because%20there%20simply%20is%20a%20huge%20breach%20in%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20foreign%20policy%20thoughts%2C%20as%20exemplified%20by%20the%20Chinese%20view%20on%20India's%20choices%20for%20neutrality.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Dr.%20Sriparna%20Pathak%20is%20an%20Associate%20Professor%20of%20China%20Studies%2C%20and%20the%20Director%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20Northeast%20Asian%20Studies%20at%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689297120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-10%2F5civ0q7g_xi-jinping_650x400_23_October_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhat-china-really-thinks-of-indias-neutrality-4204418%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20worth%20discussing%20questions%20around%20neutrality%20as%20a%20foreign%20policy%20choice%20in%202023%2C%20given%20that%20both%20India%20and%20China%2C%20once%20again%2C%20have%20largely%20chosen%20diplomatically%20neutral%20stances%20at%20the%20UN%20in%20the%20ongoing%20Russia-Ukraine%20war.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nd