y%20Thursday%20evening%20to%20eliminate%20a%20Pentagon%20policy%20that%20makes%20it%20easier%20for%20service%20members%20to%20obtain%20an%20abortion%2C%20a%20vote%20underlining%20the%20intense%20conservative%20anger%20over%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20House%20voted%20largely%20along%20party%20lines%20221-213%20in%20tacking%20on%20the%20restriction%20to%20a%20larger%20must-pass%20bill%20funding%20the%20Pentagon.%20Only%20two%20House%20Republicans%2C%20Reps.%20John%20Duarte%20of%20California%20and%20Brian%20Fitzpatrick%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20broke%20with%20the%20party.%20One%20House%20Democrat%2C%20Rep.%20Henry%20Cuellar%20of%20Texas%2C%C2%A0voted%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20measure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuarte%20is%20regarded%20as%20one%20of%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20GOP%20incumbents%2C%20though%20many%20of%20the%20other%20Republicans%20in%20this%20category%20voted%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20restrictions.%20Cuellar%20is%20often%20the%20singular%20Democrat%20to%20oppose%20abortion%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Ronny%20Jackson%2C%20a%20Texas%20Republican%2C%20proposed%20the%20amendment%20to%20a%20massive%20Pentagon%20funding%20bill%20that%20would%20end%20the%20Pentagon's%20policy%20of%20providing%20travel%20reimbursement%20to%20service%20members%20looking%20to%20obtain%20an%20abortion.%20The%20assistance%20was%20passed%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20landmark%202022%20decision%20that%20gut%20abortion%20rights.%20Some%20Republicans%20have%20blasted%20the%20Defense%20Department%20over%20the%20policy.%20Sen.%20Tommy%20Tuberville%20has%20gone%20so%20far%20as%20to%20block%20the%20confirmation%20of%20a%20new%20chairman%20of%20the%20Joint%20Chiefs%20of%20Staff%20and%20a%20leader%20for%20the%20Marine%20Corps.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20the%20White%20House%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F07%2F13%2Fbiden-tommy-tuberville-military-00106168%5C%22%3Ereportedly%20view%20the%20issue%20as%20a%20w