26quot%3BIt%20seems%20there%20is%20no%20readiness%20neither%20to%20invite%20Ukraine%20to%20NATO%20nor%20to%20make%20it%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Alliance%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThis%20means%20that%20a%20window%20of%20opportunity%20is%20being%20left%20to%20bargain%20Ukraine's%20membership%20in%20NATO%20in%20negotiations%20with%20Russia.%20And%20for%20Russia%2C%20this%20means%20motivation%20to%20continue%20its%20terror.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZelenskyy's%20tweet%20was%20likely%20in%20response%20to%20NATO%20foregoing%20a%20roadmap%20or%20timetable%20for%20Kyiv%20to%20gain%20membership.%20Instead%2C%20Ukraine%20is%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20allies%20agree%20and%20conditions%20are%20met%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20when%20its%20war%20with%20Russia%20ends.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tweet's%20a%20scathing%20callout%2C%20and%20according%20to%20the%20Post%2C%20left%20the%20US%20delegation%20%26quot%3Bfurious.%26quot%3B%20Prior%20to%20Kyiv%20arriving%2C%20there%20were%20informal%20discussions%20on%20how%20best%20to%20respond%2C%20leading%20to%20US%20officials%20suggesting%20they%20revisit%20or%20remove%20any%20mention%20of%20Ukraine's%20invitation%20to%20membership%20at%20all.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20language%20remained%20in%20the%C2%A0communiqu%C3%A9%2C%20and%20Zelenskyy's%20tone%20noticeably%20softened%20during%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20summit%20as%20NATO%20leaders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nato.int%2Fcps%2Fen%2Fnatohq%2Fnews_217059.htm%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20major%20package%20of%20military%20support%20for%20Kyiv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZelenskyy%20has%20repeatedly%20pushed%20for%20Ukraine%20to%20join%20NATO%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%20and%20has%20worked%20with%20allies%20to%20procure%20Western%20weapons%20and%20assets%20for%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20summit's%20kick-the-can%20approach%20extends%20Ukraine's%20long%20limbo%20towards%20NATO%20inclusion.%20In%202008%2C%20NATO%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C