20and%20lawmakers%20see%20a%20benefit%20in%20allowing%20each%20state%20to%20determine%20its%20own%20NIL%20standards.%20Having%20a%20more%20expansive%20state%20law%20is%20now%20an%20asset%20akin%20to%20a%20new%20practice%20facility%20or%20a%20massive%20weight%20room.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20colleges%20would%20like%20us%20to%20step%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Senate's%20top%20Republican%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%20if%20they%20don't%20come%20behind%20a%20particular%20proposal%2C%20we'll%20screw%20it%20up%20going%20through%20the%20legislative%20process.%20What%20I've%20said%20to%20them%20repeatedly%20is%20before%20we%20can%20act%2C%20we%20have%20to%20know%20what%20you%20want.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20interim%2C%20the%20NCAA%20has%20mostly%20allowed%20states%20to%20proceed%20on%20their%20own.%20College%20athletics'%20governing%20body%20has%20taken%20a%20backseat%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20landmark%20unanimous%20ruling%20in%202021%20that%20opened%20the%20door%20for%20athlete%20compensation.%20For%20years%2C%20the%20NCAA%20had%20argued%20that%20any%20whiff%20of%20compensation%20would%20tarnish%20the%20amateur%20nature%20of%20college%20sports.%20The%20ruling%20further%20undermined%20the%20NCAA's%20authority%20to%20restrict%20the%20benefits%20athletes%20can%20receive.%20In%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20decision%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fharvardlawreview.org%2Fprint%2Fvol-135%2Fncaa-v-alston%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20NCAA%20voted%20to%20allow%3C%2Fa%3E%20athletes%20to%20get%20paid%20through%20NIL.%20The%20floodgates%20were%20open.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20one%20tracker%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.saul.com%2Fnil-legislation-tracker%5C%22%3E32%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20passed%20some%20version%20of%20name%2C%20image%2C%20and%20likeness%20laws.%20Some%20states%20allow%20for%20NIL%20benefits%20for%20high-school%20athletes.%20Missouri's%20newly%20passed%20NIL%20law%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%